citation.case_name: Fellom v. Redevelopment Agency of City and County of San Francisco

html_lawbox:
358 U.S. 56 (1958)

FELLOM ET AL.
v.
REDEVELOPMENT AGENCY OF THE CITY AND COUNTY OF SAN FRANCISCO ET AL.

No. 323.

Supreme Court of United States.

Decided October 27, 1958.
APPEAL FROM THE DISTRICT COURT OF APPEAL OF CALIFORNIA, FIRST APPELLATE DISTRICT.

Appellants pro se.

Dion R. Holm and George E. Baglin for appellees.

PER CURIAM.

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.
